  So here's the deal w/ Midgard:<br>
<br>
On most Thursdays, Jamus, Rasha, ishemir and namira will be on galahad/mid. Every dagger is welcome to join us, the past 2 weeks we've had full groups. Thats very cool.  <br>
<br>
On some Mondays, Jamus, Rasha, ishemir and namira will be on galahad/mid. Every dagger is welcome to join us.<br>
<br>
The difference here is that on Mondays, anything on Palomides overwrites this, and the instant we start to outlevel the rest of the Dagger population, we'll call off Mid Monday or dedicate Mid monday to alts. <br>
<br>
In order to group effectively, you need to stay within 15% of the average level of the group. That means that, while in the teens, no one should be over 2 levels higher than the average level player. This also means that too much solo play on Galahad/Mid will quickly bump you out of &quot;groupability&quot; with the majority of the Daggers on Mid.  My suggestion is have 1 character you play w/ the Daggers on monday/thursday and have another character for solo play. I did this w/ Krujen (my hunter) and Brya (my group friendly healer).<br>
<br>
The short term goal for Mid monday/thursday is to get the bulk of us to 20 so we can go baby-RVR, which is really a lot of fun, a lot different than Emain battles.<br>
